# Util File Conventions

All utility code must follow this structure:

- Root folder: `util/` (never `utils/`)
- Group related utils in a themed subfolder: `util/<theme>/`
- Each file is named `<name>.util.ts`

## Examples

```
util/supabase/supabase.util.ts
util/date/date.util.ts
util/api/api.util.ts
util/storage/storage.util.ts
```

## Rules

- Never place util files directly in `util/` — always use a subfolder
- The subfolder name and file name should share the same theme/name
- Import using the full path: `import { supabase } from '@/util/supabase/supabase.util'`
